<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">The Twentieth Sunday After Pentecost</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Jan 13, 2015 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
I want a faith <br></br>
that is like <br></br>
a good pair of shoes.
</p>

 <p>
Comfortable, <br></br>
not too demanding, <br></br>
painless, <br></br>
and safe…
</p>

 <p>
Easy to forget…
</p>

 <p>
The kind you never <br></br>
know is there, <br></br>
with just a little Jesus, <br></br>
and not too much of the Spirit.
</p>

 <p>
A faith that trusts, <br></br>
but not too much. <br></br>
A faith that dreams, <br></br>
but not too big.
</p>

 <p>
But the living God <br></br>
does not deal in small faith <br></br>
and small dreams.
</p>

 <p>
So, here I am, Lord, <br></br>
opening up the dry, <br></br>
dusty corners of my heart.
</p>

 <p>
Let the river flow.
</p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>




